  "notes": [
    "This record catalogs Fowler's edition-level selection because that is the coherent unit encoded by CME00047; medieval documentary creators are represented separately from Fowler's editorial responsibility.",
    "Latin is primary in the records, Middle English is embedded, and Fowler's substantial modern English editorial matter is separately recorded.",
    "All 351 public SS100-linked Durham IIIF objects were cached separately: 235 complete provider-published inventories and 116 partial physical-object inventories.",
    "The manuscript images are not cleared for this project's commercial publishing workflow: exact manifests state CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 and Durham separately requires advance publication permission.",
